						span Rad<b>Edit</b>
						a#tagline(href="/code#todo.txt") Build Node.js apps together quickly.

		#body
			.panel
				.box4
					h3 Code Collaboration
					p.about RadEdit's IDE enables simultaneous editing, like Google Docs for code.
				.box4
					h3 Instant Gratification
					p.about When you save changes, RadEdit refreshes your browser.
				.box4
					h3 Real-Time Testing
					p.about The test runner sees changes and automagically runs affected tests.
				.box4
					h3 MVC Framework
					p.about Apps have a Model View Controller architecture with many available helpers. 
				br
		#use
			.panel
				.box3
					h2 Installation
					tt npm install radedit<br>node<br>&gt; require('radedit')('MyApp')
				.box3
					h2 Resources
					a.resource(href="/tutorials") Tutorials
					a.resource(href="/documentation") Documentation
					a.resource(href="https://github.com/sameubank/RadEdit") Project
				.box3
					h2 Philosophy
					ul
						li Convention over Configuration
						li Don't Repeat Yourself
						li Clean Code
						li Continuous Everything
				br
		#inside
			.panel
				.box: h2 What's inside?
				.box5
					h3 Express
					p Express is a minimal and flexible node.js web application framework, providing a robust set of features for building rich web applications.
				.box5
					h3 Socket.IO
					p Socket.IO aims to make realtime apps possible in every browser and mobile device, blurring the differences between transport mechanisms.
				.box5
					h3 ORM
					p ORM offers Object Relation Mappings for your Node.js application. It connects to MySQL, PostgreSQL, Amazon Redshift, SQLite or MongoDB.
				.box5
					h3 CoffeeScript
					p CoffeeScript is a little language that compiles into JavaScript. It exposes the good parts of JavaScript in a simple way.
				.box5
					h3 Jade
					p Jade is a terse and simple templating language that compiles to HTML. It has a strong focus on performance and powerful features.
				br
				.box5
					h3 CodeMirror
					p CodeMirror is a versatile text editor implemented in JavaScript for the browser. It comes with language modes and addons for advanced editing.
				.box5
					h3 CoffeeLint
					p CoffeeLint is a style checker that helps keep CoffeeScript code clean and consistent.
				.box5
					h3 Mocha
					p Mocha is a feature-rich JavaScript test framework running on node.js and the browser, making asynchronous testing simple and fun.
				.box5
					h3 Should
					p Should is an expressive, readable, test framework agnostic, assertion library that allows you to express how objects should behave.
				.box5
					h3 Forever
					p Forever is a simple command line tool for ensuring that a given script runs continuously (i.e. forever).
